      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies, vendors, and industries dominate Texas contracting?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense accounts for $27.7B in obligations, the Department of Homeland Security $21.9B, and the Department of Veterans Affairs $14.7B. Leading vendors include LOCKHEED MARTIN CORPORATION at $10B and MCKESSON CORPORATION at $9.7B, while top industries include Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $17.5B, Pharmaceutical Preparation Manufacturing at $9.8B, and Guided Missile and Space Vehicle Manufacturing at $9.7B."
